---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Install / Getting Started">
  <section>
    <h2>Install & build guide</h2>

    <p class="lead">This quick guide shows how to get the template running locally and how to build release artifacts.</p>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>JDK 17 or higher</li>
        <li>Android SDK (API 36 recommended) and Android Studio</li>
        <li>Node 18+ (for the website, not required for the app)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Clone the repository</h3>
      <pre style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.02);padding:10px;border-radius:8px;overflow:auto">git clone https://github.com/cmwen/min-android-app-template.git
cd min-android-app-template</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Run locally (debug)</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Open the project in Android Studio and let it sync Gradle.</li>
        <li>Use an emulator or connected device and run the Debug configuration.</li>
        <li>Alternatively, build from the terminal:</li>
      </ol>
      <pre style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.02);padding:10px;border-radius:8px;overflow:auto">./gradlew assembleDebug</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Build release APK / AAB</h3>
      <p>If you are signing the build with your own keystore, export the following environment variables before running the release task:</p>
      <pre style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.02);padding:10px;border-radius:8px;overflow:auto">export ANDROID_KEYSTORE_FILE=/path/to/keystore.jks
export ANDROID_KEYSTORE_PASSWORD=store_password
export ANDROID_KEY_ALIAS=key_alias
export ANDROID_KEY_PASSWORD=key_password
./gradlew assembleRelease
# or assembleBeta for the beta variant</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Run tests</h3>
      <pre style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.02);padding:10px;border-radius:8px;overflow:auto">./gradlew test</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Website (optional)</h3>
      <p>If you need to work on the repository website, switch to the `website/` directory and run:</p>
      <pre style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.02);padding:10px;border-radius:8px;overflow:auto">cd website
npm install
npm run dev</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Need more help?</h3>
      <p>Open an issue or pull request on the <a href="https://github.com/cmwen/min-android-app-template" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--accent)">GitHub repository</a>. For CI or release problems check `.github/workflows/`.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
